lm)|Two Lovers]]'' (1928) as The Duke of Azar\n* ''[[Hellship Bronson]]'' (1928) as Capt. Ira Bronson\n* ''[[The Godless Girl]]'' (1928) as The Brute\n* ''[[The Passion Song]]'' (1928) as John Van Ryn\n* ''[[Noah's Ark (1928 film)|Noah's Ark]]'' (1928) as Nickoloff / King Nephiliu\n* ''[[Dreary House]]'' (1928)\n* ''[[Love in the Desert]]'' (1929) as Abdullah\n* ''[[Linda (1929 film)|Linda]]'' (1929) as Armstrong Decker\n* ''False Fathers'' (1929) as Parson\n* ''[[Careers (film)|Careers]]'' (1929) as The President\n* ''[[The Four Feathers (1929 film)|The Four Feathers]]'' (1929) as Slave Trader\n* ''[[The Isle of Lost Ships (1929 film)|The Isle of Lost Ships]]'' (1929) as Captain Peter Forbes\n* ''Two O'Clock in the Morning'' (1929)\n* ''[[The Show of Shows]]'' (1929) (with [[John Barrymore]], [[Mary Astor]], [[Myrna Loy]] and [[Loretta Young]]) as Performer in \"The Pirate\" Number / Soldier (segment \"Rifle Execution\")\n* ''[[Glorifying the American Girl]]'' (1929) as Himself (uncredited)\n* ''[[Isle of Escape]]'' (1930) as Shane\n* ''[[Under a Texas Moon]]'' (1930) as Jed Parker\n* ''[[Murder Will Out (1930 film)|Murder Will Out]]'' (1930) as Lt. Concon\n* ''[[Show Girl in Hollywood]]'' (1930) as Himself at Premiere (uncredited)\n* ''[[Song of the Flame (film)|Song of the Flame]]'' (1930) as Konstantin\n* ''[[Golden Dawn (film)|Golden Dawn]]'' (1930) as Shep Keyes\n* ''[[Oh, Sailor Behave!]]'' (1930) as Romanian General\n* ''[[The Way of All Men]]'' (1930) as Stratton\n* ''[[Big Boy (film)|Big Boy]]'' (1930) as Bagby\n* ''[[Bright Lights (1930 film)|Bright Lights]]'' (1930) as Miguel Parada\n* ''[[The Love Trader]]'' (1930) as Captain Morton\n* ''[[Renegades (1930 film)|Renegades]]'' (1930) as Thurman Machwurth\n* ''[[A Soldier's Plaything]]'' (1930) as Capt. Plover\n* ''[[Tol'able David (1930 film)|Tol'able David]]'' (1930) as Luke\n* ''[[The Millionaire (1931 film)|The Millionaire]]'' (1931) as Peterson\n* ''[[Honeymoon Lane (film)|Honeymoon Lane]]'' (1931) as Tom Baggott\n* ''[[The Homicide Squad]]'' (1931) as Captain Buckley\n* ''[[Shanghaied Love]]'' (1931) as Captain 'Black Yankee' angus Swope\n* ''[[Riders of the Purple Sage (1931 film)|Riders of the Purple Sage]]'' (1931) (with [[George O'Brien (actor)|George O'Brien]] and [[Marguerite Churchill]]) as Judge Dyer\n* ''[[In Line of Duty]]'' (1931) as Jean Duchene\n* ''[[The Drifter (1932 film)|The Drifter]]'' (1932) (with [[William Farnum]]) as John McNary\n* ''[[The Stoker (1932 film)|The Stoker]]'' (1932) as Santini\n* ''[[Stranger in Town (1931 film)|Stranger in Town]]'' (1932) as J.B. Hilliker\n* ''[[Cornered (1932 film)|Cornered]]'' (1932) as Laughing Red Slavens\n* ''[[No Living Witness]]'' (1932) as Clyde Corbin\n* ''[[Out of Singapore]]'' (1932) as 1st Mate Woolf Barstow\n* ''[[The Big Stampede]]'' (1932) (with John Wayne) as Sam Crew\n* ''[[The Devil Horse]]'' (1932, Serial) as Canfield\n* ''[[The Kid from Spain]]'' (1932) as Alonzo Gomez\n* ''Long Loop Laramie'' (1932)\n* ''[[She Done Him Wrong]]'' (1933) (with [[Mae West]] and [[Cary Grant]]) as Gus Jordan\n* ''[[The Thundering Herd (1933 film)|The Thundering Herd]]'' (1933) (with [[Randolph Scott]], [[Buster Crabbe]] and [[Harry Carey (actor)|Harry Carey]]) as Randall Jett\n* ''[[The Flaming Signal]]'' (1933) as Otto Von Krantz\n* ''[[Sunset Pass (1933 film)|Sunset Pass]]'' (1933) as Marshal Blake\n* ''[[The Woman I Stole]]'' (1933) as Gen. Rayon\n* ''Easy Millions'' (1933)\n* ''[[Fighting with Kit Carson]]'' (1933, Serial) as Cyrus Kraft\n* ''[[Laughing at Life]]'' (1933) as Hauseman\n* ''[[Man of the Forest (1933 film)|Man of the Forest]]'' (1933) (with [[Randolph Scott]], [[Harry Carey (actor)|Harry Carey]] and [[Buster Crabbe]]) as Clint Beasley\n* ''[[To the Last Man (1933 film)|To the Last Man]]'' (1933) (with [[Randolph Scott]], [[Esther Ralston]] and [[Buster Crabbe]]) as Jed Colby\n* ''[[Caravan (1934 film)|Caravan]]'' (1934) as Innkeeper\n* ''[[Madame Spy (1934 film)|Madame Spy]]'' (1934) as Gen